title: Detective Pikachu (Movie)
body:
- Predictable plot, but it’s worth watching for the graphics alone (and maybe for the nostalgia too).

- I honestly could not have asked for a more realistic visual re-imagination of the Pokemon universe.

- May need a little extra work on matching the Pokemon voices though.

-Pikachu is cute as fuck, but what’s new?

[spoilers alert]

- Not gonna lie, slightly relieved that the villains were white. You can never be too trusting when it comes to American adaptations Asian-centric movies… *cough*DBZ*cough*

- The romance angle was unnecessary. Is Hollywood incapable of featuring a girl and a guy in a movie without a love-line? It’s a Pokemon movie for goodness sake.

- Love the game/anime references.

- The whole mind-switch kerfuffle at the end was low-key giving me FMA flashbacks *shudders*

- Cameo at the end was a pleasant surprise.

- Overall solid effort, I would love to watch it again just to spot all the Pokemon in the movie.

title: Movie Reviews: Pokémon Detective Pikachu
body:
Movie Reviews: Pokémon Detective Pikachu

Of all the millennial nostalgia flooding movie theaters this year, one film which piqued the most interest for me was definitely Pokémon Detective Pikachu. Live-action video game movies unfortunately don’t have the best reputation due to low quality production and crappy execution. At best, they’re forgettable, and at worst, they’re dumpster fires lost in adaptation between completely different…
